The move warning is also a response to a new Missouri law that will make it harder to sue a legal entity over housing or employment discrimination.
Earlier, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) issued warnings for travelers in Texas and Arizona after those states passed new immigration control laws that required local law enforcement to arrest people for violating immigration laws, which the ACLU said should have increased racial background checks.
