By studying its skin, researchers found that the herbivore, although covered in armor and resembling a walking tank, was apparently in significant danger from carnivorous dinosaurs.
This powerful armor-covered dinosaur used red and white camouflage to hide from predators, and it used a protective technique known as protective paint, which is also used by many animals today.
