If you're going to ask for 4,000 proposals, you should be willing to have 4,000 conversations says Russell Rat, president of consulting at management firm Kotter International, who has had to see companies make mistakes by relying too much on data collection.
Because if you don't go through with it, the staff will be like, "Did you really hear me?
You don't care about that?
If you don't care, why shouldn't I?
According to Errett, the company that now conducts monthly employee surveys at Madison Reed is able to take action on the same day someone reports a problem with Glint.
