The Ukrainian parliament has registered a draft law that would impose criminal penalties on Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, the document, registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament, implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the prison term can be extended to five years.
If the offender is detained at the border with a weapon, the prison term for the offender will be increased to eight years.
Earlier, it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians trying to enter Russia outside the established checkpoints.
Magnet is out of stock.
The second-largest food retailer Magnit has announced the opening of three new Magnit-Opts test stores, designed for small wholesale purchases.
The company's press release says that the possibility of buying goods at retail remains.
New format stores were opened in Krasnodar, Saratov and Ulyanovsk.
Their range includes about 1,5 thousand food and non-food items.
"The new service will allow companies and entrepreneurs to make purchases with financial benefits, and residents to buy products for a week or a month", - they are sure of Magnit.
Metro Cash & Carry and Selgros Cash & Carry are already operating in the small wholesale segment.
In 2017, Lenta launched a special program called Lenta pro: it offered legal entities and private entrepreneurs to make purchases at special hypermarket cash registers, receive invoices to account for costs and refund VAT.
The project focuses on the HoReCa segment, retail and office space.
In Russia, two new territories of advanced social and economic development will appear - "Abaza" and "Novotroysk".
The relevant regulations of the Russian Government will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR in the territory of the city of Abasa in the Republic of Khakassia are defined.
The city, which has 15 thousand inhabitants, will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments by residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, as well as create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities under which the "Abaza" TOR will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, includes plant breeding, livestock production, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of the "Abakan mine" LLC.
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that the HACCA had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the establishment of the TOR.
The authorities of the region of Orenburg also did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroysk, a territory of advanced social and economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the monopolis, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of the A.O. "Ural Steel", as well as create more than 2,3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities under which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fishing, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroysk became the first of the monogorps of the Orenburg region to receive the status of a TOR.
Recall that the advanced development area is an economic zone with tax incentives, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that is created to attract investment to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR are: income tax of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of not less than 7,6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential connection to various infrastructure facilities, and preferential rates on rental payments.
Loza called Manson "a little boy" and threatened to "put him in the face".
Yuri Loza expressed his outrage at the words of American rock musician Marilyn Manson, who insulted Moscow.
In an interview with Komsomolska pravda, the Russian singer called Manson "poor" and "small".
According to Loza, foreign artists who can afford such statements do not need to be invited to Russia.
Besides, Loza thinks Manson should be punished for his words.
Recall that the American artist, known for his epic acts, spoke roughly about the Russian capital at a concert in Kiev.
Earlier on Thursday, "Arguments of the Week" reported that Manson's statement was commented on by the country's producer Joseph Prigojin.
In Moscow, a policeman wounded a man in the leg while defending himself from an attack
A policeman shot a fighter in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On August 3, the police department of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs received a report of a fight on the street of Mytna, 46.
"The police arrived to break the law and disrupt the participants of the conflict", RIA Novosti reported, referring to the press service of the head of the interior ministry.
According to police, when one of the participants of the conflict attacked an interior ministry employee with a piece of glass, the policeman warned the man several times about the use of a weapon and fired a warning shot.
That didn't stop the bully, and then a law enforcement officer shot the man in the leg.
The wounded man needed to be hospitalized.
